To install Furry Tools, the recommended method is to use the provided `Setup-FurryTools.ps1` PowerShell script. 
Simply open the folder containing the project files and run the script. 
It will check for Python 3.10, install it if necessary, install all required dependencies from `requirements.txt`, 
and launch the application automatically. Ensure that PowerShell allows script execution; 
you may need to set the execution policy by running PowerShell as Administrator and executing `Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser`.

Alternatively, you can install Python 3.10 manually. After installing Python, 
open a terminal in the folder containing `requirements.txt` and run `pip install -r requirements.txt` to install the necessary dependencies. 
Once the installation is complete, launch `launch.vbs` to start Furry Tools.

This guide provides a simple and reliable way to set up Furry Tools with all required components.
